<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2024-07-30T14:17:40+00:00</updated><id>/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Java Interview Questions</title><subtitle>Blog to refresh some basic topics</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Left Join, Right Join, Self Join</title><link href="/sql/basic/2024/07/30/left-join-right-join-self-join.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Left Join, Right Join, Self Join" /><published>2024-07-30T02:20:30+00:00</published><updated>2024-07-30T02:20:30+00:00</updated><id>/sql/basic/2024/07/30/left-join-right-join-self-join</id><content type="html" xml:base="/sql/basic/2024/07/30/left-join-right-join-self-join.html"><![CDATA[<p>It’s something that I might have used once or twice in my work, but it came once in an interview so I thought I should give some more attention to it.</p>

<p>To understand these special joins, I prepared some tables:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"><span class="c1">-- Create the departments table</span>
<span class="k">CREATE</span> <span class="k">TABLE</span> <span class="n">departments</span> <span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">department_id</span> <span class="nb">SERIAL</span> <span class="k">PRIMARY</span> <span class="k">KEY</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">department_name</span> <span class="nb">VARCHAR</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">NOT</span> <span class="k">NULL</span>
<span class="p">);</span>

<span class="c1">-- Create the employees table</span>
<span class="k">CREATE</span> <span class="k">TABLE</span> <span class="n">employees</span> <span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">employee_id</span> <span class="nb">SERIAL</span> <span class="k">PRIMARY</span> <span class="k">KEY</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">employee_name</span> <span class="nb">VARCHAR</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">NOT</span> <span class="k">NULL</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="n">department_id</span> <span class="nb">INT</span> <span class="k">REFERENCES</span> <span class="n">departments</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">department_id</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="p">);</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>And some inserts:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"><span class="c1">-- Insert data into the departments table</span>
<span class="k">INSERT</span> <span class="k">INTO</span> <span class="n">departments</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">department_name</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">VALUES</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Human Resources'</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Engineering'</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Sales'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="c1">-- Insert data into the employees table</span>
<span class="k">INSERT</span> <span class="k">INTO</span> <span class="n">employees</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">employee_name</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">department_id</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="k">VALUES</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Alice'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Bob'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Charlie'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'David'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">),</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Eve'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">);</span></code></pre></figure>

